name: UnmodifiableMapMixin
comment: Mixin class that implements a throwing version of all map operations that change the Map.

[]=.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the map are disallowed.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the map are disallowed.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the map are disallowed.

putIfAbsent.name: putIfAbsent
putIfAbsent.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the map are disallowed.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the map are disallowed.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no key-value pair in the map.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one key-value pair in the map.

keys.name: keys
keys.comment:
The keys of this.

The returned iterable has efficient length and contains operations, based on collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.length and collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.containsKey of the map.

The order of iteration is defined by the individual Map implementation, but must be consistent between changes to the map.

length.name: length
length.comment: The number of key-value pairs in the map.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

values.name: values
values.comment:
The values of this.

The values are iterated in the order of their corresponding keys. This means that iterating collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.keys and collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.values in parrallel will provided matching pairs of keys and values.

The returned iterable has an efficient length method based on the collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.length of the map.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

[].comment: Returns the value for the given collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.[].key or null if collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.[].key is not in the map. Because null values are supported, one should either use collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.containsKey to distinguish between an absent key and a null value, or use the collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.putIfAbsent method.

[]=.comment:
Associates the collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.[]=.key with the given collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.[]=.value.

If the key was already in the map, its associated value is changed. Otherwise the key-value pair is added to the map.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment:
Adds all key-value pairs of collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.addAll.other to this map.

If a key of collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.addAll.other is already in this map, its value is overwritten.

The operation is equivalent to doing this[key] = value for each key and associated value in other. It iterates over collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.addAll.other, which must therefore not change during the iteration.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment:
Removes all pairs from the map.

After this, the map is empty.

containsKey.name: containsKey
containsKey.comment: Returns true if this map contains the given key.

containsValue.name: containsValue
containsValue.comment: Returns true if this map contains the given value.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment:
Applies collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.forEach.f to each {key, value} pair of the map.

Adding or removing keys from the map during iteration is not allowed.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

putIfAbsent.name: putIfAbsent
putIfAbsent.comment:
If collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.putIfAbsent.key is not associated to a value, calls collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.putIfAbsent.ifAbsent and updates the map by mapping collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.putIfAbsent.key to the value returned by collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.putIfAbsent.ifAbsent. Returns the value in the map.

Map<String, int> scores = {'Bob': 36};
for (var key in ['Bob', 'Rohan', 'Sophena']) {
  scores.putIfAbsent(key, () => key.length);
}
scores['Bob'];      // 36
scores['Rohan'];    //  5
scores['Sophena'];  //  7

The code that collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.putIfAbsent.ifAbsent executes must not add or remove keys.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment: Removes the association for the given collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.remove.key. Returns the value for collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.remove.key in the map or null if collection/dart-pkg-collection.UnmodifiableMapMixin.remove.key is not in the map. Note that values can be null and a returned null value does not always imply that the key is absent.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
